<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1451,1022,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,203,1022,1048]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation author="Grisebach, A. &amp; Schenk, A." box="[235,609,1022,1049]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" pagination="291 - 362" refId="ref6207" refString="Grisebach, A. &amp; Schenk, A. (1852) Iter Hungaricum anno 1852, susceptum, Beitrage zur Systematik der ungarischen Flora. Wiegmann's Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 18 (1): 291 - 362. https: // archive. org / details / archivfrnaturg 1801 berl" type="journal article" year="1852">Grisebach &amp; Schenk (1852: 315)</bibRefCitation>
published this taxon collected during the trip “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Iter Hungaricum anno 1852 susceptum</emphasis>
” in Transylvania (
<collectingCountry box="[465,571,1058,1085]" name="Romania" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Romania</collectingCountry>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[745,1098,1058,1084]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" refId="ref7996" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic literature 1. Ed. 2. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 1136 pp. http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 103414" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan (1976: 1007)</bibRefCitation>
, most of the 
<typeStatus box="[1247,1295,1059,1085]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">type</typeStatus>
specimens of Grisebach are deposited in GOET, where he was director of the botanical garden in Göttingen from 1875. The place of origin of 
<taxonomicName box="[238,468,1131,1157]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patens">
<emphasis box="[238,468,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Sempervivum patens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is located in the region of Banat (
<collectingCountry box="[841,944,1130,1157]" name="Romania" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Romania</collectingCountry>
) “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">auf Kalkfelsen über den Herkulesbädern, z. B. bei der Schwitzhöhle 2500’</emphasis>
[on limestone rocks above Băile Herculane, for example near the cave Grota cu Aburi, 
<quantity box="[136,213,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" unit="m" value="762.0">762 m</quantity>
].” This locality seems to be nearly the same as that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott. The" authorityYear="1852" box="[829,950,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heuffelii">
<emphasis box="[829,950,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. heuffelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(at the neighbouring cave Grota Haiducilor; see above). The herbarium specimen GOET 002328 was identified as the original material for 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1310,1239,1265]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patens">
<emphasis box="[1208,1310,1239,1265]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. patens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It bears the original label with Grisebach’s handwriting, including descriptive notes on morphology and the note “ 
<emphasis box="[1290,1444,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">
cf. 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1444,1275,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmor">S. marmor</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. [
<taxonomicName authority="Griseb." authorityName="Griseb." box="[145,404,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmoreum">
<emphasis box="[145,308,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. marmoreum</emphasis>
Griseb.
</taxonomicName>
]”. Later note “ 
<emphasis box="[563,811,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">flores ut in Jovisbarba</emphasis>
” led to the first identification “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1158,1390,1310,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[1158,1390,1310,1337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">Sempervivum hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.?”. Finally Grisebach crossed out the adjective “ 
<taxonomicName box="[640,715,1346,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[640,715,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” and added “ 
<emphasis box="[869,976,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">
<taxonomicName box="[869,942,1347,1372]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patens">patens</taxonomicName>
m.
</emphasis>
[mihi]”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Grisebach, A. &amp; Schenk, A." box="[1080,1451,1346,1373]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" pagination="291 - 362" refId="ref6207" refString="Grisebach, A. &amp; Schenk, A. (1852) Iter Hungaricum anno 1852, susceptum, Beitrage zur Systematik der ungarischen Flora. Wiegmann's Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 18 (1): 291 - 362. https: // archive. org / details / archivfrnaturg 1801 berl" type="journal article" year="1852">Grisebach &amp; Schenk (1852: 315)</bibRefCitation>
considered their new species as being intermediate between 
<taxonomicName box="[817,920,1382,1409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtum">
<emphasis box="[817,920,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. hirtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sims. Na" authorityYear="1812" box="[976,1139,1382,1409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="soboliferum">
<emphasis box="[976,1139,1382,1409]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. soboliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which might be the reason for his former identification.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1451,1022,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">
The specimen GOET 002328 consists of one whole plant with the rosette and inflorescence, and another fragment with just an inflorescence and several fragments of separated rosette leaves. The whole plant on the left is selected here as the 
<typeStatus box="[208,311,1526,1552]" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[348,449,1527,1553]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sempervivum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="10" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patens">
<emphasis box="[348,449,1527,1553]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="216">S. patens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
